                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100104">Germany</placeName>
                                </origPlace>
                                <origDate notAfter="1525" notBefore="1476"> 15th century, last quarter, or 16th century, first quarter.</origDate> Origin and dating based on the identity of the scribe.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Paul Lehmann argues that this text is written by the same hand who wrote National Library, Va 23, see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107187">Lehmann (1934)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="112" to="112" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>. If this is true then A 238 was written by the scholar <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102591">Albert Krantz</persName>(1450-1517), who was principally active in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100029">Hamburg</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100071">Rostock</placeName>. It is unknown how the manuscript ended up at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName>, but according to the old catalogues the manuscript has been in the library since at least the 17th century. In Jaches’s catalogue of 1698 (U 122) it is listed as <quote>212</quote> and in the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e) as <quote>Phil. in 4:o, no 5</quote>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
